caption: Great staff amazing customer service!

Ordered my food online for faster service. When I got to the store 15 minutes after ordering online. I was informed that my order was going to take 10 minutes. That’s a total of 25 minutes. Ordering my food in the store would be been way quicker to receive food. This location had no other customers inside. The whole point of doing things online is to have faster service especially with with Covid. I was very unhappy with the service when informing them of this.

I love Potbelly and the food is always good but there’s a young blonde guy who works at this store who NEVER wears his mask covering his nose (despite the store having up multiple signs that instruct customers to wear their mask so that covers the nose) and it makes me incredibly uncomfortable.

For those of you who considered looking at the reviews for this particular Potbelly establishment and are hoping to have your food delivered to you on time and correctly prepared with no complications, I am here to inform you that you should not, that is if, you enjoy headaches. As of today, I have ordered my food at this Potbelly establishment at 5:30 P.M. to be delivered at 6:10 P.M. As of right now, it is currently 7:36 P.M. and my food has not been delivered.  In regards to my order, I did have the coupon which allowed my entree to be free, however, this does not mean that my order should be treated differently than anyone else. This being said, there should have been a mention below or near the time in which the food was estimated to be delivered that delivery may be delayed. However, the staff working at this Potbelly establishment were not kind, as I have called them three times, the second time being hung up on, and the third time being told that my sandwich would be free, even though I had applied the coupon to make my entire entree free.  In my third call as well, they had mentioned that this whole time, my order somehow did not process through their system due to me ordering online, which has never been an issue previously before, and in regards to everything with this order, I have deemed this Potbelly establishment to be a failure when considering my overall appeal as a customer.  And in order to redeem themselves, they gave me two coupons in which each one gives me a free meal, however, both of them expired on 1/31/2018, which makes both of them worthless.  Truly, I will never go to this establishment again, and I believe you should not as well.  Sincerely, Randy Knox Andrus

I ordered from here on Uber eats and was so excited I was allowed to modify my salad to my liking especially because I was allergic to an ingredient.  But then when my order arrived they hadn’t made any of the modifications and my salad was covered in the ingredient I was allergic to so I was unable to eat the salad I had been so excited to receive and was just let down and disappointed. Why have the option to modify if the restaurant is just going to ignore it and not pay attention to what the customer wants whatsoever?
